The paper discusses the use of deep convolutional networks for visual recognition and recommendation in the context of an online store. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of large and diverse datasets, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the paper discusses the results of an image classification challenge, which suggests that it may also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
